⛽ Discrete Event Simulation of a Gas Station Queue Using AnyLogic

Overview
This project presents a **Discrete Event Simulation (DES)** model of a gas station queueing system developed using **AnyLogic Personal Learning Edition**. The simulation is based on **106 observed customer records** to analyze the queueing process, service performance, and customer flow.

Objectives
- Model the queueing process of a gas station.
- Analyze customer arrivals and service operations.
- Evaluate queue performance using Discrete Event Simulation.
- Understand the behavior of a single-service queueing system.

Tools & Technologies
- AnyLogic Personal Learning Edition
- Process Modeling Library
- Discrete Event Simulation (DES)

